        "state": "ENABLED",
        "testElementDTOList": [
          {
            "changeDate": "2024-08-27T14:31:32.990Z",
            "elementId": 1001,
            "factor": 0,
            "isOnReport": true,
            "dbId": 27705,
            "createDate": "2024-03-26T14:07:26.344Z",
            "state": "ENABLED",
            "structureId": 1000,
            "targetRawValue": "--><h4>Flow Pattern</h4>\n<br>\n\nIn this test, the trigger activation is tested. The test is passed if\n<ol>\n    <li>There is no trigger activation if the trigger function is deactivated: the frequency is then the one set on the DUT</li>\n    <li>There is trigger activation if the trigger function is activated: the frequency is then the one set on the ASL (which is higher) </li>\n    </li>\n</ol>\n<br>\n\nThe sequence for this test is:\n<br><br>\n<div style=\"text-align:center;\">\n<strong>\n(ASL) -> (Setup) -> (Exec) -> (Evaluation) -> (CleanUp)\n</strong>\n</div>\n<br>\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>(ASL)-Block:</strong>\n        Sets ASL values according to the product requirements.\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>(Setup)-Block:</strong>\n        Sets predefined values according to the product requirements.\n    </li>\n    \n    <li><strong>(Exec)-Block:</strong>\n        <ol>\n            <li>Starts ventilation</li>\n            <li>Waits for 20 seconds</li>\n        </ol>\n    </li>\n\n    <li><strong>(Evaluation)-Block:</strong>\n        <ol>\n            <li>The rate is measured to check wether breathes are triggered or not </li>\n            </li>\n\n        </ol>\n    </li>\n\n    <li><strong>(CleanUp)-Block:</strong>\n        Stops ventilation\n    </li>\n\n</ul>\n<br><br>\n<br><!--",
            "targetTolerance": null,
            "typeId": 1002,
            "targetSelection": null,
            "invertResult": false
          }
        ],
        "title": "(DescriptionBody)",
        "titleType": "STANDARD",
        "parameters": { "parameters": [], "rows": [] }
      },
